<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7457> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7457" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator, 55? Münzer assumed that he was a senator on the uncertain ground that he knew of Cato's proposal in the Senate that Caesar should be delivered over to the Usipetes and Tencteri for his breach of the sacred law regarding legates (Plut. Caes. 22.3; cf. Cat. Min. 51.1-2; App. Celt. frag. 18)." .
